					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">bunnyboy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But most people aren't looking for a super mapper, they are looking for something around MMC3 level. </div>
<br />
<br />That's what I meant.  If we could have a MMC3/VRCIV/VI clone, that would be nice. I would stop cracking up game and just use that instead.
<br />
<br />I don't want to "improve" the <span class="posthilit">graphics</span>, just want to be able to have more space and more functionality to be able to make some fan game similar to the platformer in the end of the nes era. Which mean some split screen, some extra counter if the need arise. But it doesn't mean that I will use all the features: it just good to know that I have access to them if I feel like it.
<br />
<br /> I have no interest in a one screen game with almost no artwork at all, I always personally hated those ones.  I started to like nes games when stories and side scrolling elements were added.</div>

